Samsung Engineering Wins $360 Million Order From Exxon’s Unit

-- B y   S a n g i m   H a n
-- 
2011-08-07T07:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-07/samsung-engineering-wins-360-million-order-from-exxon-s-unit.html
Samsung Engineering Co. and its
Indonesian partner, Tripatra Engineering won, won a $750 million
order from  Exxon Mobil Corp. (XOM) ’s unit to build production
facilities at the Banyu Urip field in the Cepu oil and gas block
in Java.  The order enables them to handle all procedures, ranging
from design to procurement, construction and pilot operations
for completion by July 2014, Samsung said in an e-mailed
 statement . The order for Samsung is worth $360 million. The deal
was also announced on Aug. 5 by  Indonesia ’s oil and gas
regulator BPMigas.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sangim Han in Seoul at 
 sihan@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
